@Location:	Boston , MA USA
@Situation:	Home Visit 5
@Activities:	Letter writing with mother
@Transcriber:	Eliza Whitbeck , Brenda Kurland
@Warning:	you can tell what Chi's name is since one of the people he's writing to has the same name
*INV:	what I would like is +//.
%mor:	pron|what-Int-S1 pron|I-Prs-Nom-S1 aux|would-Fin-S verb|like-Inf-S aux|be-Fin-Ind-Pres-S3 +//.
%gra:	1|0|ROOT 2|4|NSUBJ 3|4|AUX 4|1|ACL-RELCL 5|1|COP 6|1|PUNCT
@Comment:	BCN Dear Brian , Dear Christopher , Dear Nikki , Hi! I miss you. Love , Chris
@Comment:	Chi first attempt at a letter is to write out the alphabet. Mot then is able to get Chi on task to write a real letter. Mot gives Chi most of the ideas for the letter and Chi goes along with her. Chi decides to write to three friends of his. Although she must also give spellings of words , MOT emphasizes punctuation , capital letters , indenting , and other aspects of letter writing. Sometimes she takes the pencil from him to erase something. Chi often has to erase what he wrote but only once does he get frustrated. Mot helps Chi with spelling and sometimes asks him to sound out a word. Mot suggests a couple of different things to write in the letter and Chi chooses one of them. Mot has Chi read back parts of letter , then he reads the whole thing back at the end. The activity runs smoothly but is lengthy.
@Comment:	Time is 3:11
